    Capacitor `FilePicker` plugin manifest.

    Empty by design: ACTION_OPEN_DOCUMENT is permissionless — the
    system file picker handles the actual filesystem access on the
    app's behalf and only returns a content:// URI we are allowed to
    read once. The plugin then immediately copies the picked stream
    into app-private storage (`getFilesDir()/models/import-staging/`),
    so it never needs READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE or persistable URI grants.

    This keeps the plugin compatible with the future `offline` product
    flavor (PR 17), which strips INTERNET from the merged manifest.
-->
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android" />
